olive oil
1 packet chicken drumsticks
2 potato
1 tin sweetcorn
1 bag slaw mix
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
1 packet Peri Peri Sauce
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet mayonnaise
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• In a baking dish, combine chicken drumsticks, All-American spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bake for 20 minutes.
• Remove from oven, turn drumsticks and spoon over any juices. Bake until golden brown and cooked through, a further 15-20 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly, this adds flavour to the dish!

• Meanwhile, cut potato into fries. Drain the sweetcorn.
• In a medium bowl, combine slaw mix and a drizzle of red wine vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

• Place potato and sweetcorn on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over Aussie spice blend, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Bake until just tender, 20-25 minutes.
• When fries and corn have 5 minutes remaining, remove tray from oven, sprinkle fries with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake until melted.
• When the chicken is done, add peri peri sauce and sweet chilli sauce to the baking dish and turn to coat.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Divide Portuguese chicken drumsticks, cheesy potato fries, sweetcorn and slaw between plates.
• Pour remaining peri peri sauce from baking dish over drumsticks.
• Serve with a dollop of mayonnaise. Enjoy!